From: Colin Ian King <colin.king@canonical.com>
Date: Fri, 28 Jun 2019 12:07:05 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] mm/page_idle.c: fix oops because end_pfn is larger than
 max_pfn
References: bnc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 5.1.16
Git-commit: 7298e3b0a149c91323b3205d325e942c3b3b9ef6

commit 7298e3b0a149c91323b3205d325e942c3b3b9ef6 upstream.

Currently the calcuation of end_pfn can round up the pfn number to more
than the actual maximum number of pfns, causing an Oops.  Fix this by
ensuring end_pfn is never more than max_pfn.

This can be easily triggered when on systems where the end_pfn gets
rounded up to more than max_pfn using the idle-page stress-ng stress test:

